  "identifier": "SB 847",
  "title": "SB 847 - Current law prohibits the state lottery from approving any lottery game based on the outcome of sporting events.  This act repeals such prohibition, provided that the maximum ticket price shall not exceed five dollars per ticket.\r\n\r\n\tAdditionally, the act authorizes the Lottery Commission to use an internet application to sell electronic scratcher games, draw games, and pull-tab games where a player may access such application using a personal device.\r\nJOSH NORBERG",
